I work for a different hotel chain and have pretty high standards!	Pool area was great as was the breakfast but by Marriott standards - this was certaintly not a category 5 hotel.	Continental breakfast was standard.	The price is standard for winter in Key west.	To keep it fair; the rooms are not brand new but they are clean and in good repair.	This hotel was the cheapest of the chains hotels and we really weren't sure about the accomodations.	The standard rooms are very small and do not have any room to store luggage.